Co-operative Bank of Kenya Ltd. (COOP) , the
East African nationâ€™s fourth-biggest lender by assets, headed
for the highest in a week after  Business Daily  reported the bank
plans to create new shares to raise capital for expansion.  The stock of Co-op Bank, as the lender is known, rose as
much as 2.3 percent to 17.90 shillings before trading 0.9
percent higher at 17.65 shillings as of 12:43 p.m. in the
capital, Nairobi.  Co-op Bank sent a letter to shareholders seeking approval
to create 1.3 billion new shares, taking the number of shares to
5 billion, the Nairobi-based newspaper reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
